snippet.textDisplay:
Hello, vet tech here! Avocado is NOT toxic to cats or dogs. They are not affected by the persin in it, at least in quantities that are consumable. If they ate pounds and pounds of avocado, they may have a reaction, but just a few bites or even a whole fruit (minus pit) would most likely be fine. Now, they are very fatty, so best to avoid them in pets in general as the high fat content could lead to pancreatitis. Also, consumption of the pit could lead to an intestinal obstruction. BUT! They are very poisonous to birds! Birds and large animals (horses, goats, etc) really have to watch out avocados.


Also please spay and neuter your pets! Millions of pets die each year in shelters and on the streets due to overpopulation.
snippet.textOriginal:
Hello, vet tech here!  Avocado is NOT toxic to cats or dogs.  They are not affected by the persin in it, at least in quantities that are consumable.  If they ate pounds and pounds of avocado, they may have a reaction, but just a few bites or even a whole fruit (minus pit) would most likely be fine.  Now, they are very fatty, so best to avoid them in pets in general as the high fat content could lead to pancreatitis. Also, consumption of the pit could lead to an intestinal obstruction.  BUT! They are very poisonous to birds!  Birds and large animals (horses, goats, etc) really have to watch out avocados.


Also please spay and neuter your pets!  Millions of pets die each year in shelters and on the streets due to overpopulation.
